column10: description:{"en":"In the middle of the 19th century
column11: Japan was still closed off from the outside world. There were just the beginning signs of reformation in the long regime of Shogun Tokugawa.\nIn the remote countryside
column13: a young boy named Ryoma is growing up in a lower-class Samurai family. A decade later
column14: he is to become on of the leading figures to topple the Shogun's reign and open Japan to the western world. Our story begins with Ryoma
column15: a dreaming kid of seven years. Ryoma is an honest and tenderd-hearted boy who hates any sort of violence and brutality.\nHe is so sensitive
column17: that he often cries from pity when he sees even the simples act of violence such as another kid trampling a tiny insect. The kids and even his family call him a \"cry baby\". However
column18: he is not a coward - not a \"chicken\" at all. His distress comes from a desire to prevent unreasonable acts and the wrong doings in life. His older sister is the only person who understands his depth. She recognizes that her brother is gifted with a special talent and she does her best to protect him and cheer him up."}

zh-hk:"世界的和平遭到邪神「塞科內恩」破壞。

人類和妖精生下的「半妖精」——「尼洛」
在襁褓時期便失去雙親，
由一對人類奴隸夫妻收養。

尼洛生長在一個奴隸不被當人看的世界，
在痛失雙親以後，
肩負起照顧兩名年幼妹妹的重責大任。

只有一個方法能讓他擺脫奴隸身分、保護兩個妹妹，
那就是從奴隸出身的現任皇帝
「梅蘭」的母校「艾斯卡儂」畢業!

只不過，身為奴隸的尼洛似乎找不到
進入「艾斯卡儂」就讀的辦法...

他究竟能不能擺脫絕望，成功進到「艾斯卡儂」呢?
